com.ltsllc.miranda.clientinterface.basicclasses

Interface Equivalent

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DeadLetterQueue, Delivery, Event, MirandaObject, NodeElement, NodeStatus, Subscription, SubscriptionEntry, Topic, User

    public interface Equivalent
    Classes that implement this interface have the ability to determine if they refer to the same thing.

    If an instance of this interface returns true when isEquivalentTo(Object) is called, then they refer to the same thing. One may be a more recent version of the thing.

    Another way of looking at it is two objects can be "primary key equivalent" but not #equals(Object) equivalent.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean isEquivalentTo(java.lang.Object o)
      Return true if the receiver refers to the same thing as the argument.

    • Method Detail

      • isEquivalentTo

        boolean isEquivalentTo(java.lang.Object o)
        Return true if the receiver refers to the same thing as the argument.

        Two instances are equivalent if

        • The have the same class
        • Their "primary keys" are the same

        For example, if two users have the same user name, they are equivalent, but if the user has changed their email address then equals will return false.

        Parameters:
        o - The other instance to compare against.
        Returns:
        True if the other instance is equivalent to the receiver, false otherwise.
